This paper presents a new type of language model that can explicitly model entities, dynamically update their representations, and contextually generate their mentions. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as language modeling, coreference resolution, and entity prediction. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses entity prediction, which is a task related to information retrieval and search engines, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
